The paper addresses the problem of video object segmentation, which is a computer vision task, hence it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category. The paper proposes a novel approach based on discriminative online learning, which involves designing a specialized loss and customized optimization techniques, indicating that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The paper also mentions the use of segmentation networks, which suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the paper involves designing a segmentation network that operates at a high frame rate, indicating that it could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) category.
